{{modal-target}}

<div class="v-container">
  {{#from-elsewhere name="tools" as |tools|}}
    <div class="topbar">
      {{#liquid-bind tools rules=toolsAnimationRules as |t|}}
        {{component t}}
      {{/liquid-bind}}
    </div>
  {{/from-elsewhere}}

  <div class="container">
    <main>
      <p>This app demonstrates the <a href="https://github.com/ef4/ember-elsewhere">Ember Elsewhere</a> addon. It contains three elsewhere targets:</p>

      <ol>
        <li>The blue sidebar is a target named "right", implemented as <code>\{{from-elsewhere name="right"}}</code>.</li>

        <li>The green toolbar (visible only on some pages) is a target named "tools", implemented with a <code>\{{#from-elsewhere}}</code> component that allows it to be composed with liquid-fire animations.</li>
        <li>There is a "modal" target that demonstrates animated modals. See the button on {{#link-to "component.third"}}Third Page{{/link-to}}.</li>
        <li>There is an "actions" target, implemented with a <code>\{{#multiple-from-elsewhere name="actions"}}</code> that allows you to pass multiple components. Check {{#link-to "component.fourth"}}Fourth Page{{/link-to}}.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>As you use the links below to switch between the three routes, each route can choose to place content into either of the sidebars by including <code>\{{in-sidebar}}</code>. </p>

      <nav>
        {{#link-to 'component.index'}}First Page{{/link-to}}
        {{#link-to 'component.second'}}Second Page{{/link-to}}
        {{#link-to 'component.third'}}Third Page{{/link-to}}
        {{#link-to 'component.fourth'}}Fourth Page{{/link-to}}
      </nav>

      {{outlet}}
    </main>

    <div class="right-sidebar">
      {{from-elsewhere name="right"}}
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="bottom-bar">
    {{#multiple-from-elsewhere name="actions" as |c|}}
      <div class="action">
        {{component c}}
      </div>
    {{/multiple-from-elsewhere}}
  </div>
</div>
